98Disease%20X'%20is%20a%20placeholder%20for%20an%20unknown%20pathogen%20that%20could%20cause%20a%20global%20emergency.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnHistory%20has%20taught%20us%20that%20we%20must%20anticipate%20new%20threats.%20Failing%20to%20prepare%20leaves%20the%20world%20prepared%20to%20fail.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FWEF24%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23WEF24%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%2C%20I%20spoke%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FWHO%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40WHO%3C%2Fa%3E%20initiatives%20that%20are%20supporting%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FM4uF44WYNj%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FM4uF44WYNj%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Tedros%20Adhanom%20Ghebreyesus%20(%40DrTedros)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrTedros%2Fstatus%2F1747736510135160897%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2017%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''There%20are%20things%20that%20are%20unknown%20that%20may%20happen%2C%20and%20anything%20happening%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20when%2C%20not%20if%2C%20so%20we%20need%20to%20have%20a%20placeholder%20for%20that%2C%20for%20the%20diseases%20we%20don't%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Ghebreyesus%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-v-7dd7fde0%3E%26quot%3BWe%20lost%20many%20people%20%5Bduring%20COVID%5D%20because%20we%20couldn't%20manage%20them.%20They%20could%20have%20been%20saved%2C%20but%20there%20was%20no%20space.%20There%20was%20not%20enough%20oxygen.%20So%20how%20can%20you%20have%20a%20system%20that%20can%20expand%20when%20the%20need%20comes%3F''%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%20that%20the%20WHO%20has%20already%20started%20implementing%20measures%20to%20prepare%20for%20another%20outbreak%20including%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20pandemic%20fund%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20''technology%20transfer%20hub''%20in%20South%20Africa.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''Equity.%20It%20was%20a%20serious%20problem.%20Many%20high-income%20countries%20were%20hoarding%20vaccines.%20To%20address%20the%20equity%20problem%2C%20we%20established%20the%20mRNA%20technology%20transfer%20hub%20in%20South%20Africa.%20This%20is%20to%20increase%20the%20local%20production...%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20data-v-7dd7fde0%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20Disease%20X%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-v-7dd7fde0%3EDisease%20X%20is%20not%20a%20specific%20disease%20but%20is%20the%20name%20of%20a%20potential%20virus%20similar%20to%20COVID-19.%20It%20could%20be%20a%20new%20agent%2C%20a%20virus%2C%20a%20bacterium%2C%20or%20a%20fungus%20without%20any%20known%20treatment.%20The%20global%20health%20body%20has%20categorised%20the%20unknown%20disease%20among%20Covid-19%2C%20Ebola%2C%20Lassa%20fever%2C%20Middle%20East%20respiratory%20syndrome%20(MERS)%2C%20Nipah%2C%20and%20Zika%2C%20which%20have%20already%20caused%20widespread%20fatalities%20during%20outbreaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(23)00348-1%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Lancet%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0said%20that%20the%20WHO%20formally%20started%20using%20the%20term%20in%202018%2C%20which%20represents%20the%20next%20unknown%20disease%20of%20epidemic%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews%2Fitem%2F21-11-2022-who-to-identify-pathogens-that-could-cause-future-outbreaks-and-pandemics%5C%22%3EWHO%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20November%202022%20mentions%20that%20Disease%20X%20is%20included%20to%20indicate%20an%20unknown%20pathogen%20that%20could%20cause%20a%20serious%20international%20epidemic.%C2%A0According%20to%20WHO%2C%20worldwide%2C%20the%20number%20of%20potential%20pathogens%20is%20very%20large%2C%20while%20the%20resources%20for%20disease%20research%20and%20development%20(R%26amp%3BD)%20are%20limited.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2F