n%20checks.%20Early%20signs%20include%20changes%20in%20moles%2C%20such%20as%20irregular%20borders%20or%20color%20variations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20LIFESTYLE%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Flife-style%2Fhealth-fitness%2Fhealth-news%2Fduchess-of-york-sarah-ferguson-diagnosed-with-skin-cancer%2Farticleshow%2F107044950.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court's%20Role%20in%20January%2022%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22113449%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20is%20well%20known%20by%20now%2C%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESri%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20Mandir%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Ayodhya%20is%20to%20be%20held%20today%2C%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20set%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dnaindia.com%2Findia%2Freport-ram-temple-inauguration-pm-modi-full-itinerary-for-ayodhya-visit-on-jan-22-3075123%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einaugurate%20the%20temple%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20This%20is%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20temple%20that%20is%20the%20result%20of%20decades%20of%20movement%20by%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20what%20finally%20enabled%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20at%20Ayodhya%20was%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20historic%20order%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etitle%20dispute.%20It%20was%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20five-judge%20bench%2C%20claiming%20to%20be%20speaking%20in%20one%20voice%2C%20gave%20legitimacy%20to%20the%20Hindu%20side%E2%80%99s%20claim%2C%20ultimately%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20judgment%20is%20historic%20not%20just%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20it%20%E2%80%98settled%E2%80%99%20the%20dispute%20that%20has%20shaped%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%2C%20social%2C%20and%20cultural%20landscape%20for%20a%20while%20now%2C%20but%20also%2C%20in%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it%20dealt%20with%20the%20tradition%20of%20legal%20methods%20of%20looking%20at%20history.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReading%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgement%20as%20a%20scholar%20as%20well%20as%20a%20law%20practitioner%20gives%20one%20enough%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20became%20a%20party%20to%20the%20historical%20movement%E2%80%99s%20culmination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20must%20be%20said%20that%20right%20from%20the%20outset%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fayodhya-verdict-supreme-court-judgment%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20judgement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20appears%20to%20be%20based%20on%20two%20very%20interesting%20arguments.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFirst%2C%20it%20gives%20reasonable%20arguments%20where%20it%20sees%20the%20entire%20disputed%20structure%20%E2%80%93%20the%20area%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20mosque%20and%20the%20area%20surrounding%20it%20%E2%80%93%20as%20two%20separate%20parts%2C%20namely%20the%20outer%20and%20the%20inner%20courtyard%2C%20while%20giving%20its%20pronouncement%20for%20the%20outer%20courtyard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Secondly%2C%20it%20simultaneously%20treated%20the%20same%20structure%2C%20which%20it%20earlier%20saw%20as%20divided%20into%20the%20inner%20and%20the%20outer%2C%20as%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ecomposite%20whole%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20while%20giving%20its%20judgement%20for%20the%20inner%20courtyard.%20Both%20reasonings%20were%20used%20by%20the%20court%20to%20conclude%20the%20arguments%20in%20favour%20of%20one%20side%3A%20the%20Hindu%20side.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20begin%20with%2C%20the%20entire%20%E2%80%98disputed%20structure%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20it%20was%20called%2C%20was%20divided%20into%20two%20parts%20by%20the%20court%3A%20the%20inner%20and%20the%20outer%20courtyard.%20Once%20this%20division%20was%20done%2C%20the%20court%20set%20itself%20the%20task%20of%20looking%20into%20the%20possession%20claims%20of%20the%20two%20parties%20and%20their%20individual%20claims%20to%20the%20outer%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20inner%2C%20courtyard.%20The%20apex%20court%2C%20then%2C%20was%20tasked%20with%20accessing%20the%20claims%20of%20both%20the%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20sides%20based%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98possessory%20title%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20set%20itself%20to%20examine%20the%20evidence%20offered%20by%20both%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim%20sides%20to%20the%20different%20courtyards.%20Despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20court%2C%20on%20multiple%20occasions%2C%20stated%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Ctitle%20cannot%20be%20established%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20faith%20and%20belief%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(para.%201209)%2C%20a%20careful%20reading%20of%20the%20judgement%20reveals%20that%20the%20court%20essentially%20deviated%20from%20factual%20and%20evidential-based%20approaches%20to%20legal%20methods%20and%20sought%20refuge%20in%20Hindu%20faith%20and%20belief.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fthe-babri-masjid-demolition-went-unpunished-and-the-fight-for-justice-died%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520fight%2520for%2520justice%2520in%2Cthe%2520illegality%2520of%2520the%25201992%5C%22%3EThe%20Babri%20Masjid%20Demolition%20Went%20Unpunished%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Fight%20for%20Justice%20Died%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArguments%20for%20t%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3Ehe%20outer%20courtyard%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20begin%2C%20in%20its%20very%20line%20of%20inquiry%2C%20the%20court%20adopted%20different%20reasoning%20to%20access%20different%20parties%E2%80%99%20claims%20to%20both%20the%20two%20courtyards.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20becomes%20evident%20when%20one%20looks%20at%20how%20the%20court%20deals%20with%20the%20claims%20of%20the%20outer%20courtyard%20from%20both%20sides.%20Based%20on%20different%20travelogues%20that%20the%20court%20accepted%20as%20evidence%2C%20the%20court%20accepted%20the%20reasoning%20for%20continuous%20and%20unimpeded%20worship%20in%20the%20courtyard%20by%20the%20Hindus.%20While%20doing%20so%2C%20it%20relied%20on%20Jospeh%20Tieffenthaler%E2%80%99s%20travelogues%20and%20his%20tour%20to%20India%20in%20the%20year%201740.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20travelogue%20included%20sections%20that%20mention%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfaith%20and%20belief%20of%20Hindus%2C%E2%80%9D%20who%20associated%20the%20erstwhile%20structure%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20with%20the%20birthplace%20of%20the%20deity%20Ram.%20The%20court%20accepted%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cthe%20account%20has%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20form%20of%20worship%E2%80%A6%20and%20to%20the%20assembly%20of%20devotees%20at%20the%20site.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Further%2C%20the%20court%20refers%20to%20the%20writings%20of%20Montgomery%20Martin%2C%20who%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfaith%20and%20belief%20of%20Hindus%2C%E2%80%9D%20attributes%20the%20structure%20as%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Ram.%20The%20writings%20of%20Tieffenthaler%20and%20Martin%20are%20relied%20upon%20by%20the%20court%20as%20evidence%20to%20illustrate%20the%20site%E2%80%99s%20long%20history%20of%20Hindu%20worship.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20court%20interprets%20the%20presence%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESita%20%3Cem%3Erasoi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eswargdwar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20the%20%3Cem%3Eb%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3Eedi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20described%20in%20Tieffenthaler%E2%80%99s%20account%2C%20as%20proof%20for%20the%20Hindu%20sides%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9Copen%2C%20exclusive%2C%20and%20unimpeded%20possession%20of%20the%20outer%20courtyard.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20assessing%20the%20Muslim%20side%E2%80%99s%20occupancy%20of%20the%20same%2C%20the%20court%20notes%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20Muslim%20side%20to%20prove%20their%20sole%20occupancy%2C%20dismissing%20their%20claim%20for%20uninterrupted%20possession%20of%20the%20site%20based%20on%20their%20absence%20from%20the%20site.%20The%20reasoning%20for%20their%20absence%2C%20which%20was%20a%20result%20of%20their%20being%20disallowed%20to%20pass%20through%20the%20outer%20courtyards%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20Hindu%20priests%20worshipping%20and%20living%20there%2C%20was%20left%20untouched%20by%20the%20court.%20That%20the%20Muslims%20were%20forcibly%20ousted%20from%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20outer%20courtyard%20and%20were%20denied%20entry%20by%20force%20by%20Hindus%20who%20had%20taken%20over%20possession%20of%20it%20does%20not%20become%20reasonable%20enough%20to%20be%20accepted%20by%20the%20court.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20court%20accepts%20various%20accounts%20of%20travellers%2C%20historical%20records%20are%20dealt%20with%20differently.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20court%20does%20not%20rely%20on%20the%20Waqf%20Inspector%20report%20of%20December%201949%2C%20which%20stated%20that%20the%20priests%20who%20worshipped%20and%20lived%20in%20the%20outer%20courtyard%20obstructed%20Muslims%20from%20passing%20through%20it.%20It%20was%20because%20of%20this%20that%20only%20the%20Friday%20namaz%20could%20be%20performed%20inside%20the%20mosque%2C%20and%20that%20too%20with%20the%20assistance%20of%20the%20police.%20In%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20the%20court%20chose%20to%20ignore%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20demonstration%20of%20uninterrupted%20possession%20of%20the%20outer%20courtyard%20must%20be%20impossible%20for%20the%20Muslim%20side.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20declared%20the%20outer%20courtyard%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Hindu%20side.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-babri-masjid-judgment-and-the-sound-of-silence%5C%22%3EThe%20Babri%20Masjid%20Judgment%20and%20the%20Sound%20of%20Silence%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArguments%20for%20t%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3Ehe%20inner%20courtyard%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EComing%20to%20the%20inner%20courtyard%2C%20the%20court%20accepted%20the%20submissions%20of%20the%20Hindu%20side%2C%20placing%20reliance%20on%20the%20accounts%20of%20the%20travellers%20who%20cited%20oral%20testimonies%20of%20Hindu%20devotees%2C%20indicating%20that%20large%20groups%20of%20Hindu%20devotees%20visited%20the%20site%20on%20Hindu%20religious%20holidays.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%20court%2C%20these%20testimonies%20established%20a%20pattern%20of%20actual%20worship%20over%20the%20years%20as%20these%20devotees%20would%20stand%20at%20the%20railing%20of%20a%20brick%20wall%20structure%20%E2%80%93%20a%20division%20that%20separated%20the%20inner%20and%20outer%20courtyard%20%E2%80%93%20to%20offer%20their%20prayers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETaking%20note%20of%20the%20evidence%20that%20demonstrated%20the%20continuation%20of%20namaz%20inside%20the%20dome%20%E2%80%93%20the%20last%20namaz%20having%20been%20performed%20on%20December%2016%2C%201949%20%E2%80%93%20the%20court%20accepted%20the%20submissions%20made%20by%20the%20Muslim%20side%20that%20it%20continued%20to%20be%20in%20possession%20of%20the%20inner%20courtyard.%20The%20court%20also%20admitted%20a%20contestation%20over%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20mosque%20that%20once%20led%20to%20its%20damage%20in%201934%2C%20which%20was%20repaired%20and%20renovated%20by%20a%20Muslim%20contractor%2C%20indicative%20of%20the%20assertion%20of%20Muslims%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20pray%20inside%20the%20inner%20courtyard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Even%20though%20the%20Muslim%20side%20presented%20papers%20demonstrating%20historical%20records%20of%20grants%20from%20the%20British%20government%20for%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20upkeep%20and%20preservation%20as%20proof%20of%20its%20continued%20possession%2C%20the%20court%20sought%20evidence%20from%20the%20Muslim%20side%20for%20nearly%20500%20years%20prior%20to%201857.%20The%20unreasonable%20reasoning%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20apply%20to%20the%20Hindu%20side.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Hindu%20side%20could%20not%20produce%20any%20direct%20evidence%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20uninterrupted%20usage%20and%20actual%20possession%20inside%20the%20structure%2C%20the%20Muslims%20were%20here%20able%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20actual%20worship%20inside%20the%20structure%2C%20as%20indicated%20above.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20here%20comes%20the%20most%20interesting%20detour%20by%20the%20court.%20It%20stated%20that%20the%20structure%20was%20actually%20not%20in%20parts%20but%20a%20composite%20whole.%20The%20same%20court%20that%20accepted%20P.%20Carnegy%E2%80%99s%20written%20accounts%20of%201870%2C%20which%20noted%20that%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20brick-grill%20wall%20by%20the%20British%20government%20in%201857%20divided%20the%20premises%20into%20two%20parts%20now%20accepted%20a%20theory%20of%20the%20structure%20being%20a%20composite%20whole.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20new%20theory%20gave%20the%20court%20an%20easy%20way%20out%2C%20wherein%20it%20concluded%20that%20since%20Hindus%20had%20continued%20to%20perform%20worship%20at%20the%20site%20and%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20mosque%20also%20could%20not%20impede%20them%2C%20the%20entire%20structure%20would%20go%20to%20the%20Hindu%20side.%20This%20conclusion%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20was%20based%20on%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebalance%20of%20probabilities.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20alternative%20argument%20that%20claimed%20that%20the%20British%20government%E2%80%99s%20construction%20of%20the%20brick-grill%20wall%20in%201857%20predetermined%20the%20title%20was%20also%20summarily%20rejected%20by%20the%20court.%20Instead%2C%20the%20court%20provided%20a%20different%20interpretation%20that%20read%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20grill-brick%20wall%20did%20not%20constitute%20either%20a%20subdivision%20of%20the%20disputed%20site%2C%20which%20was%20one%20composite%20property%2C%20nor%20did%20it%20amount%20to%20a%20determination%20of%20title%20by%20the%20colonial%20administration.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20Ayodhya%20Judgment%20Means%20for%20the%20Future%20of%20the%20Republic%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fsupreme-court-ayodhya-babri-masjid-ram-janambhoomi%5C%22%3EWhat%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Ayodhya%20Judgment%20Means%20for%20the%20Future%20of%20the%20Republic%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20sum%20up%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20stood%20at%20the%20site%20until%20it%20was%20illegally%20demolished%20on%20December%206%2C%201992%2C%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20in%20the%20case%20highlights%20its%20quest%20for%20evidence%20to%20support%20its%20argument%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Hindu%20side.%20The%20aforementioned%20interpretation%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20illustrates%20the%20use%20of%20different%20criteria%20for%20different%20sides%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20disdain%20for%20the%20evidence%20presented%20by%20the%20Muslim%20side.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20This%20is%20how%20unreasonable%20reasoning%20brought%20about%20the%20end%20of%20one%20of%20the%20oldest%20controversies%20in%20Indian%20history.%20Today%2C%20as%20we%20witness%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20at%20the%20Ram%20temple%2C%20we%20must%20ask%20the%20court%20a%20simple%20question%3A%20if%20the%20mosque%20had%20still%20been%20standing%2C%20would%20it%20have%20presented%20justifications%20for%20its%20%E2%80%98legal%E2%80%99%20demolition%20and%20ordered%20for%20the%20same%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20once%20again%20hearing%20the%20Gyanvyapi%20mosque%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Fsupreme-court-stays-execution-of-allahabad-hc-order-on-shahi-idgah-land-survey-11705383412571.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EShahi%20Idgah%20disputes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20one%20wonders%20if%20the%20Ram%20temple%20movement%20has%20truly%20culminated%20and%20its%20dust%2C%20settled.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EKawalpreet%20Kaur%20is%20a%20practicing%20advocate%20based%20in%20Delhi.%20She%20is%20associated%20with%20Human%20Rights%20Law%20Network%2C%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705903558000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22113449%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fthe-supreme-courts-role-in-january-22%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20had%20still%20been%20standing%2C%20would%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20have%20presented%20justifications%20for%20its%20%E2%80%98legal%E2%80%99%20demolition%20and%20ordered%20for%20the%20same%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fthe-supreme-courts-role-in-january-22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Akash%20Ambani%20Said%20After%20Reaching%20Ayodhya%20For%20Ram%20Temple%20Event