n%20Constitution%2C%20described%20politics%20in%20India%20as%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%20but%20theology%20in%20action%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20representative%20government%20is%20so%20weak%20when%20operating%20among%20European%20peoples%2C%20where%20the%20secularisation%20of%20politics%20has%20gone%20far%20further%2C%20how%20much%20weaker%20must%20it%20be%20in%20India%20where%20politics%20is%20nothing%20but%20theology%20in%20action.%20It%20is%20this%20theology%20against%20which%20the%20depressed%20classes%20must%20seek%20to%20be%20protected%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2FImages%2Fattach%2Famb%2FVolume_02.pdf%5C%22%3Esaid.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20words%20on%20the%20politics%20in%20India%20being%20%E2%80%9Ctheology%20in%20action%E2%80%9D%20are%20to%20be%20believed%2C%20a%20manifestation%20of%20his%20statement%20will%20be%20visible%20on%20January%2022%2C%20when%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20sovereign%2C%20secular%20state%20in%20India%2C%20participates%20in%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20just%20months%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fram-temple-ayodhya-government-modi-action-meat-hospital-half-day%5C%22%3Eofficial%20sanction%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20event%20at%20the%20under-construction%20Ayodhya%20Ram%20temple%20%E2%80%93%20built%20on%20the%20site%20where%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fthe-babri-masjid-demolition-inalterably-changed-the-trajectory-of-indias-history%5C%22%3EBabri%20Masjid%20was%20destroyed%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Hindutva%20groups%2C%20with%20over%202%2C000%20people%20killed%20in%20the%20ensuing%20communal%20violence%2C%20over%20three%20decades%20ago%20%E2%80%93%20is%20in%20no%20uncertain%20terms%20being%20celebrated%20as%20a%20national%20one%20with%20state%20governments%20including%20central%20hospitals%20rolling%20out%20official%20notifications%2C%20orders%20and%20directions%20giving%20half%20or%20full%20day%20offs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%20essay%2C%20political%20theorist%20Rajeev%20Bhargava%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F24479049%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20secularism%20is%20not%20against%20religion%2C%20it%20opposes%20institutionalised%20religious%20domination.%20He%20wrote%20that%20the%20secular%20state%20shows%20%E2%80%9Ccritical%20respect%20to%20all%20religious%20and%20philosophical%20world%20views%2C%20possible%20only%20when%20it%20adopts%20a%20policy%20of%20principled%20distance%20towards%20all%20of%20them%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoes%20the%20January%2022%20event%20then%20represent%20an%20unprecedented%20moment%20in%20independent%20India%20where%20this%20%E2%80%9Cprincipled%20distance%E2%80%9D%20between%20the%20state%20and%20religion%20is%20obfuscated%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSecularism%20as%20principled%20distance%20is%20being%20brutally%20crushed%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bhargava%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20current%20conjuncture%2C%20secularism%20is%20out%20of%20the%20picture.%20Secularism%20has%20been%20abandoned.%20Hardly%20a%20moment%20for%20any%20kind%20of%20celebration.%20Once%20secularism%C2%A0%20is%20set%20aside%2C%20the%20relevant%20question%20is%20what%20kind%20of%20a%20religion%20centred%20state%20is%20replacing%20a%20secular%20state%3F%20Here%20there%20are%20three%20possibilities%3A%20one%20is%20theocracy.%20In%20a%20classic%20theocracy%2C%20a%20religious%20head%20such%20as%20the%20Shankaracharya%20should%20become%20PM.%20But%20this%20is%20not%20being%20witnessed.%20In%20the%20second%20kind%20of%20religious%20centred%20state%2C%20there%20is%20a%20very%20close%20alliance%20between%20the%20big%20leaders%20of%20a%20religious%20community%20and%20the%20state.%20Both%20the%20religious%20and%20the%20political%20leaders%20are%20virtually%20equal%20partners%20in%20running%20the%20state.%20This%20too%20is%20not%20happening%20here.%20Then%20what%20is%20it%3F%20It%20appears%20that%20there%20is%20a%20third%20model.%20Here%2C%20the%20state%20has%20merged%20with%20religion%20entirely%20on%20its%20own%20terms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2012%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20Modi%20announced%20in%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1745691500179263899%5C%22%3E%20audio%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20will%20be%20starting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffeeding-cows-sleeping-on-floor-pms-11-day-ritual-ahead-ram-temple-event-4891699%5C%22%3E11-day%20rituals%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20event%20and%20said%20that%20God%20had%20%E2%80%9Cmade%20him%20the%20representative%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20present%20at%20the%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20reminds%20me%20of%20the%20Divine%20Rights%20of%20the%20King%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Bhargava.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20somebody%20who%20is%20acting%20like%20the%20king%20and%20has%20announced%20that%20divinity%20is%20passing%20through%20him%20or%20he%20is%20chosen%20by%20God%2C%20by%20the%20divine%20voice%20to%20perform%20this%20ceremony.%20This%20is%20a%20total%20subsumption%20of%20religion%20by%20politics.%20The%20line%20between%20the%20religion%20and%20the%20state%20has%20been%20broken%20down%20and%20is%20breaking%20down%20entirely%20at%20the%20initiative%20of%20the%20state%20which%20is%20dictating%20how%20religion%20and%20religious%20ceremonies%20are%20to%20be%20conducted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fravi-shankar-prasad-india-will-never-be-a-theocracy-the-state-will-be-neutral-treat-all-religions-equally-9118222%2F%5C%22%3E%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20former%20Union%20minister%20and%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20Ravi%20Shankar%20Prasad%20upon%20being%20asked%20on%20the%20blurring%20lines%20between%20religion%20and%20state%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CFelicitating%20the%20grand%20ceremony%2C%20arranging%20for%20that%20does%20not%20mean%20blurring%20the%20lines%E2%80%A6%20The%20prime%20minister%20is%20going%20there%20as%20a%20real%20worshipper%20of%20Lord%20Ram%2C%20and%20he%20is%20following%20the%20required%20discipline%20for%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHilal%20Ahmed%2C%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Developing%20Societies%20said%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20constitutional%20morality%20becomes%20crucial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20event%20can%20be%20seen%20from%C2%A0two%20different%20perspectives.%20One%20could%20argue%20that%20this%20is%20actually%20a%20cultural%20event.%20The%20active%20participation%20of%20political%20leaders%20representing%20the%20state%20authority%2C%20hence%2C%20may%20be%20interpreted%20as%20an%20acceptable%20act%20on%20legal%20technical%20grounds.%20Many%20BJP%20leaders%20are%20making%20arguments%20of%20this%20kind.%20We%20must%20remember%20that%20in%20the%20Indian%20context%2C%20giving%20money%20to%20a%20mosque%20or%20a%20temple%20or%20politician%20going%20to%20religious%20events%20are%20acceptable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20there%20is%20another%20way%20to%20look%20at%20this%20event.%20The%20idea%20of%20constitutional%20morality%20becomes%20crucial%20in%20this%20regard.%20It%20is%20expected%20from%20the%20state%20to%20maintain%20a%20principled%20distance%20from%20religious%20affairs.%20Two%20questions%20might%20be%20raised%20here%3A%20is%20it%20possible%20to%20disassociate%20religious%20elements%20from%20the%20inauguration%20ceremony%3F%20Is%20it%20a%20religious%20event%20or%20not%3F%20Secondly%2C%20are%20people%20of%20all%20religions%20going%20to%20be%20included%20in%20this%20celebration%20or%20would%20they%20feel%20excluded%3F%20From%20this%20perspective%2C%20it%20might%20deviate%20from%20the%20distinctiveness%20of%20the%20idea%20of%20secularism%20and%20constitutional%20morality%20in%20the%20Indian%20context.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21194425%2FGEW5biYaEAAZLb1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21194425%2FGEW5biYaEAAZLb1.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21194425%2FGEW5biYaEAAZLb1-300x221.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21194425%2FGEW5biYaEAAZLb1-1024x753.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693919%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22883%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20at%20the%20Kothandaramaswamy%20Temple.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20opposition%20INDIA%20alliance%20has%20decided%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20the%20event%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20they%20have%20instead%20found%20alternative%20ways%20to%20platform%20their%20Hindu%20identity.%20The%20Congress%20announced%20its%20decision%20to%20not%20attend%20the%20ceremony%20in%20Ayodhya%20calling%20it%20a%20BJP-RSS%20event%2C%20but%20former%20party%20president%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20will%20be%20visiting%20a%20temple%20in%20Assam%20during%20his%20ongoing%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra.%20West%20Bengal%20chief%20minister%20and%20Trinamool%20Congress%20chief%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20will%20hold%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffor-january-22-mamata-banerjee-plans-communal-harmony-rally-4873659%5C%22%3Eharmony%20rally%20in%20Kolkata%20%3C%2Fa%3Ebut%20only%20after%20visiting%20a%20Kali%20Temple%20in%20Kolkata.%20The%20Delhi%20government%20under%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20is%20organising%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fdelhi%2Fdelhi-govt-to-organise-3-day-ramlila-9118242%2F%5C%22%3Ethree-day%20Ram%20Lila%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20the%20national%20capital%2C%20while%20Shiv%20Sena%20(Uddhav%20Thackeray%20fact)%20will%20see%20former%20Maharashtra%20chief%20minister%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20in%20Nashik%20where%20he%20will%20offer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fuddhav-thackeray-gets-ram-mandir-invite-speed-post-sanjay-rauts-ravan-swipe-at-bjp-2491620-2024-01-21%5C%22%3Eprayers%20at%20the%20Kalaram%20Temple.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmed%20said%20that%20while%20the%20political%20discourse%20might%20be%20centred%20around%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20other%20political%20parties%20needs%20to%20be%20looked%20at%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20on%20the%20Ayodhya%20title%20suit%20was%20based%20on%20a%20certain%20legal%20technicality.%20It%20didn%E2%80%99t%20subscribe%20to%20Hindutva%20claims.%20If%20you%20read%20the%20judgement%2C%20you%20find%20that%20the%20court%20invokes%20secular%20legal%20principles.%20It%20gives%20land%20to%20the%20party%20representing%20the%20Ram%20Lalla%20Virajman.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20recognises%20the%20destruction%20of%20Babri%20Masjid%20as%20a%20criminal%20act%20and%20asks%20the%20state%20to%20give%20five%20acres%20of%20land%20to%20construct%20a%20new%20mosque.%20Nobody%20is%20talking%20about%20these%20details.%20The%20entire%20political%20class%20gives%20us%20the%20impression%20that%20the%20court%20has%20accepted%20the%20Hindutva%20claim%20and%20for%20that%20reason%20Hindutva%20politics%20is%20invincible.%20The%20Opposition%20wants%20to%20break%20the%20monopoly%20of%20BJP%20on%20Hindutva%20or%20for%20that%20matter%20Ram%20Temple.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Verma%2C%20fellow%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Research%20(CPR)%2C%20said%20that%20the%20event%20presents%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdilemma%E2%80%9D%20for%20other%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20they%20go%20there%20it%20is%20a%20problem%20if%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20then%20also%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20problem.%20That%20is%20why%20it%20is%20a%20dilemma%20for%20them.%20And%20there%20is%20no%20easy%20answer.%20But%20this%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20helpful.%20They%20should%20think%20real%20hard%20on%20this%20question%20and%20think%20about%20what%20their%20politics%20on%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%2C%20so%20they%20are%20only%20reacting%20at%20the%20moment.%20Of%20course%20if%20your%20opponent%20is%20in%20a%20dilemma%20it%20helps%20the%20BJP%20but%20only%20time%20will%20tell%20whether%20it%20will%20bring%20votes%20or%20not.%20But%20the%20opposition%20is%20in%20a%20bind%20on%20this%20question%20and%20there%20is%20no%20doubt%20about%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Ahmed%2C%20in%20post%202014%20India%2C%20the%20political%20class%20has%20lost%20interest%20in%20the%20politics%20of%20secularism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20secularism%20has%20become%20irrelevant%20in%20the%20context.%20People%20adhere%20to%20secular%20values%20in%20various%20ways.%20Politically%20speaking%2C%20the%20BJP%20would%20like%20to%20use%20the%20Ayodhya%20celebration%20for%202024%20elections.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20party%20is%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20as%20a%20political%20issue.%20There%20is%20a%20serious%20competition%20for%20Hindu%20votes.%20Every%20political%20party%20is%20interested%20in%20capitalising%20on%20Hindu%20sentiments.%20So%20BJP%20is%20not%20the%20only%20party%20which%20will%20use%20Hindutva%20for%20political%20gains%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMridula%20Mukherjee%2C%20former%20professor%20of%20history%20at%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20and%20former%20director%20of%20Nehru%20Memorial%20Museum%20and%20Library%2C%20said%20that%20January%2022%20represents%20a%20new%20turn%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20post-independence%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20about%20the%20prime%20minister%20attending%20the%20event%20but%20it%20is%20much%20more.%20He%20is%20actually%20the%20main%20character%20in%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%2C%20he%20is%20performing%20religious%20functions.%20Inaugurating%20a%20temple%20is%20very%20different%20from%20performing%20religious%20functions%20in%20the%20consecration%20ceremony.%20In%20my%20understanding%20it%20is%20not%20within%20the%20permissible%20framework%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMukherjee%20said%20that%20while%20it%20is%20a%20religious%20event%20in%20which%20a%20temple%20is%20being%20consecrated%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20purpose%20to%20which%20it%20is%20being%20put%20is%20clearly%20political%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20classic%20sense%20the%20use%20of%20religion%20for%20political%20gains%20is%20what%20we%20call%20communalism%2C%20whether%20Hindu%20or%20Muslim%20or%20Christian%20or%20Jew.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705847445000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21194322%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-01-21-at-1.25.07-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpm-modi-in-ram-temple-pran-prathishtha-end-of-secularism-as-distance-between-state-and-religion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20January%2012%2C%20Modi%20announced%20that%20he%20will%20undertake%2011-day%20rituals%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20and%20said%20that%20God%20had%20%E2%80%9Cmade%20him%20the%20representative%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20present%20at%20the%20ceremony.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22e